{"title": "India\u2019s spice scare a wake-up call to review food safety", "tags": "opinion", "timestamp": "2024-06-17", "content": "KOLKATA \u2013 The allure of Indian spices has been timeless. They attracted European colonial traders to the country several centuries ago and helped lay the ground for ancient maritime trade. Even today they remain in demand, powering India\u2019s rise as the world\u2019s largest spice exporter, with more than $5.6 billion worth of masala shipped worldwide each year.\nBut that longstanding image of India as a coveted source of spices took a walloping recently when certain spice products from two well-known Indian brands were recalled in Singapore and Hong Kong for containing unsafe levels of ethylene oxide."}